{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": "You are a Go engineer working on a Kubernetes operator.\nThe repository is located at /Users/kpais/kpais-workspace/a_b_evals/repos/multiarch-tuning-operator-treatment.\nChange your working directory to that repository before beginning.\n\nTask:\nAdd a new optional int32 field MaxImageInspectionRetries to ClusterPodPlacementConfigSpec\nin api/v1beta1/clusterpodplacementconfig_types.go. Apply kubebuilder markers:\nminimum value of 1, maximum value of 20, and a default of 5.\n\nThen update the image inspection retry logic in internal/controller/podplacement/pod_model.go\nto read this value from the CPPC informer singleton (via pkg/informers/clusterpodplacementconfig/)\ninstead of any hardcoded constant.\n\nAlso update the v1alpha1 conversion so the new field round-trips correctly across API versions.\n\nFinally, state which make targets must be run after the API change and in what order.\n\n\nProduce a complete implementation. Include:\n- All files that must be modified with the exact changes\n- Any make targets or commands to run and in what order\n- The complete code for any new files or functions"}, "timestamp": "2026-07-20T17:00:35.603Z"}
