t, so I need to update the `maxRetries()` method to fetch it from there while maintaining backward compatibility with the tests.\n\nFor the field conversion between v1alpha1 and v1beta1, since v1alpha1 doesn't have this field, I'll use an annotation pattern similar to how `FallbackArchitecture` is handled, adding a `MaxImageInspectionRetriesAnnotation` and implementing the conversion logic in `ConvertTo` and `ConvertFrom` methods.\n\nOn the field type itself, I'm leaning toward `*int32` rather than `int32` with omitempty because it gives a cleaner distinction between \"not set\" and \"set to zero,\" even though kubebuilder defaults will ensure the API server sets it to 5 when not provided.\n\nNow I'll write out the full implementation, including the v1alpha1 conversion logic that stores and restores the int32 value as a string in an annotation using strconv.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2010,"cache_read_input_tokens":58434,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2010,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"568c625e-56a8-4dfa-a9ed-5b68a4365921","uuid":"396333a1-07cc-44ee-9c61-ffc89f407ec1","timestamp":"2026-07-20T17:02:10.640Z","request_id":"req_vrtx_011CdDfk1MBnqG3GFHmp8zUd"}
